Palo Alto High School's Spirit Week started off with Theme Day today, where each grade level dressed in unique yet unifying costumes: seniors in '90s attire, juniors in pirate costumes, sophomores in soccer-related gear, and freshmen in costumes inspired by Disney's "The Lion King." For more information about today's events, <a href="http://palyvoice.com/2014/10/25/preview-spirit-week-kicks-off-with-theme-day/">click here</a>.

Each grade held a meeting earlier in the year where it voted upon a theme that matched its class color. Although the seniors chose "The Great Gatsby" as their green-related theme, seniors wore '90s clothes on Theme Day to follow the tradition of dressing as the decade that they were born in.

[slideshow post_id=77239]

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

The Paly Voice recapped the Day One lunch rally of Spirit Week 2014.  The "Minute to Win It" activities included "Nose Dive," "Banana Bump" and "Shake It." Click <a href="https://sites.google.com/site/pahsasb/sw2014" target="_blank">here</a> for the Palo Alto High School Associated Student Body's master document for more information.

&nbsp;

